{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/uk-national-screening-committee/about/recruitment","content_id":"1fdfe136-0fec-437c-955b-a3de82500958","description":"Information about working for the UK National Screening Committee (UK NSC) and links to sites where our jobs are advertised.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>There are several different ways you can work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr>: <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-nsc-code-of-practice/uk-nsc-code-of-practice#appointing-new-uk-nsc-members\">become a member of the committee</a>, join one of the committee’s <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-national-screening-committee/about/our-governance#expert-and-advisory-groups\">expert reference groups</a> that advise on specific areas, or work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"become-a-member-of-the-committee\">Become a member of the committee</h2>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The committee currently has no vacancies.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-national-screening-committee/about/our-governance#uk-national-screening-committee-uk-nsc\">committee membership</a> normally includes individuals from public life, academia and practising clinicians who have expertise in one or more relevant areas. Members of the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> are appointed for a fixed term as individuals and not as representatives of any organisations, after which time the role is open to new applicants, who can apply through the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/\">Civil Service Jobs</a> website.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"become-a-member-of-a-uk-nsc-expert-reference-group\">Become a member of a <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> expert reference group</h2>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> expert reference groups currently have no vacancies.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3 id=\"applying-for-reference-group-vacancies\">Applying for reference group vacancies</h3>\n\n<p>To apply for a reference group vacancy (when advertised), you should submit an expression of interest and a biography (up to 500 words or an A4 page) detailing your relevant experience and engagement with screening and how you can contribute to the workings of the reference group.  </p>\n\n<p>Email your application form or any enquiries to <a href=\"mailto:uknsc@dhsc.gov.uk\">uknsc@dhsc.gov.uk</a>. Please use the reference group name and post title in your email subject line.</p>\n\n<p>If you do not receive an acknowledgement of your application within 5 working days, please get in touch.  </p>\n\n<p>Applications will be reviewed by a panel of the reference group, including the chair and 2 members of the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat team. </p>\n\n<p>We will assess the application forms against the skills and experience outlined above and make our selection on that basis. Shortlisted applicants will be invited to a telephone interview.  </p>\n\n<p>All applications will receive a successful or unsuccessful notification. The successful candidates will receive information about next steps.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"work-for-the-uk-nscs-secretariat\">Work for the <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr>’s secretariat</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat is based in the Department of Health and Social Care and provides specialist and administrative support to the committee.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n  <p>The <abbr title=\"UK National Screening Committee\">UK NSC</abbr> secretariat currently has no vacancies. Vacancies are advertised through the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/\">Civil Service Jobs</a> website.</p>\n</div>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"Deadline for applications to expert group vacancies closed.","public_timestamp":"2025-10-24T10:48:14Z"},{"note":"Positions advertised with UK NSC expert reference groups. Closing date 6 October 2025.","public_timestamp":"2025-09-08T08:27:40Z"},{"note":"Adverts now closed for secretariat vacancies","public_timestamp":"2023-09-29T13:17:41Z"},{"note":"Addition of adverts for 7 SEO evidence review posts.","public_timestamp":"2023-08-09T10:44:01Z"},{"note":"Vacancies advertised on UK NSC secretariat for Modelling Lead, Research Lead, Targeted Screening Lead and Information Science and Horizon Scanning Lead \r\n","public_timestamp":"2023-07-25T14:15:20Z"},{"note":"Recruitment deadline has ended for ARG and FMCH vacancies.","public_timestamp":"2023-04-24T07:52:32Z"},{"note":"Deadline extended for expert group vacancy applications.","public_timestamp":"2023-04-06T08:04:24Z"},{"note":"Publicising vacancies in ARG and FMCH","public_timestamp":"2023-03-17T08:20:24Z"},{"note":"Removed the UK NSC vacancies as the deadline has passed.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-30T14:57:53Z"},{"note":"Reinstated the UK NSC membership recruitment information as the deadline has been extended.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-23T14:18:09Z"},{"note":"Removed the UK NSC vacancies as the deadline has passed.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-23T11:48:09Z"},{"note":"Deadline for UK NSC member recruitment campaign extended until 23 September.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-16T10:18:16Z"},{"note":"Reference group vacancies added.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-10T14:53:06Z"},{"note":"Added 12 current vacancies for UK NSC members.","public_timestamp":"2021-08-26T12:36:41Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2